    <item>
      <title>Jamming Wi-Fi with `mdk4`</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/wifi-jam-tutorials-by-mdk3_mdk4_aireplayng/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/wifi-jam-tutorials-by-mdk3_mdk4_aireplayng/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;With the &lt;code&gt;mdk4&lt;/code&gt; tool, you can jam Wi-Fi networks in various ways. This guide will walk you through the installation, setup, and usage of &lt;code&gt;mdk4&lt;/code&gt;, including examples for different attacks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-installation&#34;&gt;1. Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If &lt;code&gt;mdk4&lt;/code&gt; is not installed on your system, install it using the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt-get install mdk4 -y
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;switching-to-root-user&#34;&gt;Switching to Root User&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are not the root user, switch to root:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo su
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;kali@gajendra:~$ sudo su
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-checking-network-interface-status&#34;&gt;2. Checking Network Interface Status&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check your network interface status to see if it&amp;rsquo;s in monitor mode:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Table of Contents</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/archlinux/interface_managing_guide/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/archlinux/interface_managing_guide/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;airmon-ng&#34;&gt;Airmon-ng&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To start monitoring mode on wlan0:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airmon-ng start wlan0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;iwconfig&#34;&gt;iwconfig&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To enable monitor mode using iwconfig:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo ifconfig &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;INTERFACE&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; down
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo iwconfig &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;INTERFACE&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; mode monitor
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo ifconfig &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;INTERFACE&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; up
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;iw&#34;&gt;iw&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To enable monitor mode using iw:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo ip link &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;INTERFACE&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; down
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo iw &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;INTERFACE&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; monitor control
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo ip link &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;INTERFACE&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; up
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;adding-a-new-monitor-interface&#34;&gt;Adding a New Monitor Interface&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To add a new monitor interface:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo iw &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;INTERFACE&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; interface add &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;NEW_INTERFACE&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; monitor
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;aircrack-ng-installation&#34;&gt;Aircrack-ng Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To install aircrack-ng:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt-get update
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt-get install aircrack-ng
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;airmon-ng-commands&#34;&gt;Airmon-ng Commands&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To use airmon-ng commands:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Wi-Fi Handshake Capture Guide using aircrack-ng Tools</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/wi-fi-handshake-capture-guide-using-aircrack-ng-tools/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/wi-fi-handshake-capture-guide-using-aircrack-ng-tools/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-1-scan-available-wifi-networks&#34;&gt;üîç 1. Scan Available WiFi Networks&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;-scan-all-nearby-wifi-networks&#34;&gt;üåê Scan all nearby WiFi networks&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airodump-ng mon0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;-scan-only-24-ghz-networks-80211bg&#34;&gt;üì∂ Scan only 2.4 GHz networks (802.11b/g)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airodump-ng --band &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;bg&lt;/span&gt; mon0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;-scan-only-5-ghz-networks-80211a&#34;&gt;üì° Scan only 5 GHz networks (802.11a)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airodump-ng --band a mon0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;-band-option-summary&#34;&gt;üìã Band Option Summary&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band a&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí 5 GHz (802.11a)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band b&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí 2.4 GHz (802.11b)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band g&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí 2.4 GHz (802.11g)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band bg&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí All 2.4 GHz (recommended)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band abg&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí Both 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-2-capture-wpawpa2-handshake&#34;&gt;üéØ 2. Capture WPA/WPA2 Handshake&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;-start-listening-on-target-ap&#34;&gt;üéØ Start listening on target AP&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Replace &amp;lt;channel&amp;gt;, &amp;lt;BSSID&amp;gt;, and &amp;lt;output_filename&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airodump-ng -c &amp;lt;channel&amp;gt; --bssid &amp;lt;BSSID&amp;gt; -w &amp;lt;output_filename&amp;gt; mon0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Example&lt;/p&gt;</description>
